<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id4761b69f-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s7473"><num value="7473">§ 7473.</num><heading> Disposition of fees</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Except as provided in sections 7470A and 7475, all fees received by the Tax Court pursuant to this title shall be deposited into a special fund of the Treasury to be available to offset funds appropriated for the operation and maintenance of the Tax Court.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id4761b6a0-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">(<ref href="/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736">Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/68A/888">68A Stat. 888</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/99/514/tXV/s1553/b/2">Pub. L. 99–514, title XV, § 1553(b)(2)</ref>, <date date="1986-10-22">Oct. 22, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/2754">100 Stat. 2754</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/114/113/dQ/tIV/s432/b">Pub. L. 114–113, div. Q, title IV, § 432(b)</ref>, <date date="2015-12-18">Dec. 18, 2015</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/129/3126">129 Stat. 3126</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id4761b6a1-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id4761b6a2-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id4761b6a3-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2015—<ref href="/us/pl/114/113">Pub. L. 114–113</ref> amended section generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “Except as provided in section 7475, all fees received by the Tax Court shall be covered into the Treasury as miscellaneous receipts.”</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1986—<ref href="/us/pl/99/514">Pub. L. 99–514</ref> substituted “Except as provided in section 7475, all” for “All”.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id4761b6a4-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDateOfAmendment" id="id4761b6a5-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date of 1986 Amendment</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Amendment by <ref href="/us/pl/99/514">Pub. L. 99–514</ref> effective <date date="1987-01-01">Jan. 1, 1987</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/99/514/s1553/c">section 1553(c) of Pub. L. 99–514</ref>, set out as an Effective Date note under <ref href="/us/usc/t26/s7475">section 7475 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
